HEADWORD: Amiability
<hw>A`mi*a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
of being amiable; amiableness; sweetness of disposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every excellency is a degree of <qex>amiability</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amiable</ent>⟦br⟧
